<section class="hero">
  <h1>Bull &amp; Bear <em>Cycles</em></h1>
  <div class="hero-subtitle">The volatility is the price of the returns &mdash; you cannot buy one without paying the other.</div>
  <p class="subtitle">Bitcoin has delivered the best returns of any major asset and the deepest drawdowns of any major asset. These are not two facts. They are <em>one</em> fact, seen from two sides. This page holds both at once &mdash; and refuses to tell you where the bottom is.</p>
</section>

<main class="content-area">

  {% include 'components/tool-framing.njk' %}

  <!-- ════════ HOOK — return and volatility are one fact ════════ -->
  <div class="section-intro bb-prose">
    <p>Over 2014&ndash;2024, Bitcoin was the <strong>best-performing major asset in eight of eleven years</strong> &mdash; and the <strong>worst-performing in the other three</strong> (BlackRock). That single line is the whole thesis. The engine that produced roughly <strong>136% compound annual growth since inception</strong> is the same engine that produced four drawdowns of 77% or more. You do not get the ascent without the falls; they are the up-swing and the down-swing of one oscillation.</p>
    <p>So this page does not try to sell you the returns while hiding the pain, or scare you with the pain while hiding the returns. It puts them side by side, grades its own evidence, and &mdash; on the one question everyone actually wants answered, <em>where is the bottom?</em> &mdash; it deliberately declines to guess. The honesty is the point. <strong>If a claim here has a caveat, the caveat is printed next to it, at the same size.</strong></p>
  </div>

